<hw>an"a*bas</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n"⟦adot⟧*b⟦acr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'anaba`s</grk>, p. p. of <grk>bai`nein</grk> to
advance.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of fishes, remarkable
for their power of living long out of water, and of making their way on
land for considerable distances, and for climbing trees; the climbing
fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

